@keith-turner I was trying to get accumulo time stamp, could you please point me on How to find the first 3 bits of it? And also do I have to convert long datatype to binary format to do that? I did the following so far.

```
@Test(expected=IllegalArgumentException.class)
 public void testStampConstructor() {
 Stamps stamps = localClient.getTimestamps(new Long(4242),10);
 long txStampsStart = stamps.txStampsStart;
 long  gcStamp = stamps.gcStamp;  
 }
```

@adepuravikrishna could do something like the following in the test

```java
Test(expected=IllegalArgumentException.class)
testBadStartTime(){
   new Stamp(1<<62, 5)
}

Test(expected=IllegalArgumentException.class)
testBadGcTime(){
   new Stamp(5,1<<62)
}
```

@jkosh44 you need to fork the apache repo, push your changes to your fork, and then create a pull request.  You are trying to push to the apache repo instead of your forked repo.  If you have already forked look into the `git remote add` command.   Also look into pushing to specific remote.

https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo/
